AddRowToTable(HtmlNode, HtmlNode)

Adds a new definition to the specified HTML definitionList. The definition is created from the provided HtmlNode, and cells are extracted based on specific criteria. If the definition is determined to be a header definition, the cells will be created with the 'th' tag; otherwise, they will be created with the 'td' tag.

public static void AddRowToTable(HtmlNode tableNode, HtmlNode rowNode)

Parameters

tableNode HtmlNode

The HtmlNode representing the definitionList to which the definition will be added.

rowNode HtmlNode

The HtmlNode representing the definition that will be added to the definitionList. The definition should contain span elements with class 'C9DxTc' and not contain nested span elements with class 'Apple-tab-span'.

GetList(HtmlNode)

Creates a new HTML list node by extracting list items from the provided node. If a list item contains more than one span element, the content of the first span is wrapped in a bold ('b') tag. The resulting list structure is returned as an HtmlNode.

public static HtmlNode GetList(HtmlNode node)

Parameters

node HtmlNode

The HtmlNode representing the list to be processed. Must not be null.

Returns

HtmlNode

An HtmlNode containing the newly created list structure.

Remarks

The method specifically looks for 'li' elements within the provided node and processes 'span' elements within each list item. Note that the method currently ends with a 'NotImplementedException', indicating that it may not be complete.

Exceptions

ArgumentNullException

Thrown if the provided node is null.

NotImplementedException

Thrown as the method is not fully implemented.

ParseSectionContent(HtmlNode)

Parses the content of a given HTML section node, extracting specific elements such as headings, lists, and paragraphs. If the content contains definitionList data, it is organized into a definitionList structure within the returned node.

public static HtmlNode ParseSectionContent(HtmlNode node)

Parameters

node HtmlNode

The HtmlNode representing the section to be parsed.

Returns

HtmlNode

An HtmlNode containing the parsed content, organized into a 'div' element, with any definitionList data structured into 'definitionList' elements.

Remarks

The method specifically looks for the following elements within the section: h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6, ul, ol, and p. If definitionList data is detected, it is handled using the WOINWebPageHelper.ContainsTableData and WOINWebPageHelper.AddRowToTable methods.
